PUBLIC Protector Busisiwe Mkhwebane will take up her grievances with Sunday Times and Vytjie Mentor privately.Mkhwebane has denied claims made by the paper on Sunday that she opened a case against former public protector Thuli Madonsela.Kgalalelo Masibi, the public protector&rsquo;s spokeswoman, said Mkhwebane requested that police investigate the alleged leak of Madonsela&rsquo;s interview with President Jacob Zuma about state capture allegations. Masibi said Mkhwebane was worried the alleged leak could compromise the trust the public had in her office.She said this was the only information she had shared with Sunday Times, and it was not clear how the newspaper had interpreted the information. Mkhwebane was saddened by former ANC MP Vytjie Mentor&rsquo;s response to the article. Mentor accused Mkhwebane of being a liar, and promised to lay charges against the new public protector.